  "id": "38131",
  "title": "Bug 38131ajc needs -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage",
  "description": "Bug 38131ajc needs -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Steps to reproduce: 

1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile using the following command: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

   You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

   Expected behavior: The compiled class file should be placed in the existing "subpackage" directory without creating a new "subpackage" directory.

   This behavior aligns with the behavior of the javac command.",
  "OB": "When compiling a class from a subpackage using the command "ajc subpackage\Test.java," the compiler creates a new "subpackage" directory under the existing "subpackage" directory instead of placing the compiled class file in the existing "subpackage" directory.",
  "EB": "The compiled class file should be placed in the existing "subpackage" directory without creating a new "subpackage" directory.",
  "SR": "1. Create a class in a subpackage.
2. Compile the class using the command "ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java"."
}
